kies   microsoft credit capital investments llc home about us contact us cci snapshot team affiliations about us while our core investing principles remain constant we have a history of innovation interweaving our human capital with technology the name “teak hill” evokes the idea of both timeless strength and resilience   credit capital’s senior team is comprised of investment management and asset management professionals who excelled in previous leadership positions at respected institutions they are complemented by experienced managers analysts and staff together they form a closeknit team who are significant investors in our offerings alongside our limited partners and shareholders   credit capital investments is a registered investment adviser with the united states securities and exchange commission                         copyright   credit capital investments llc all rights reserved credit capital investments llc home about us contact us contact us credit capital investments llc  john f kennedy parkway nd floor short hills new jersey    tel   fax     email investorrelationscreditcicom                 copyright   credit capital investments llc all rights reserved credit capital investments llc home about us contact us contact us credit capital investments llc  john f kennedy parkway nd floor short hills new jersey    tel   fax     email investorrelationscreditcicom                 copyright   credit capital investments llc all rights reserved credit capital investments llc home about us contact us cci snapshot team affiliations team donald tang chairman varkki chacko managing principal chief investment officer robert murray cfa principal chief compliance officer dr suhas ketkar principal richard roy principal portfolio manager joseph pirrello jd cpa chief financial officer   donald tang chairman     donald tang is the chairman of credit capital investments cci he acts as a catalyst for cci’s development efforts additionally he provides indepth expertise and relationships with financial intermediaries and institutions donald’s international reach is strengthening our efforts to further promote the teak hill fund outside of the united states   donald previously served as vice chairman of bear stearns  co inc donald joined bear stearns  co inc in  in los angeles as senior managing director in  he was appointed president and chief executive officer of bear stearns asia—he later was named chairman donald was elected to the board of directors of bear stearns  co inc in  and was named vice chairman in  donald was named chairman and president of bear stearns international holdings in    donald is also vice chairman of qri an oil  gas technology company he serves on the boards of numerous civic cultural and educational institutions he is currently a trustee at california institute of technology member of the committee of  and member of advisory committee of harvard university asia center he is chairman emeritus and honorary trustee of the asia society southern california   donald has completed his bs in chemical engineering from the california state university polytechnic of pomona california and did his undergraduate work at the east china institute of technology in shanghai   varkki chacko managing principal chief investment officer     varkki chacko is the chief investment officer and the managing principal of credit capital investments cci he chairs cci’s investment committee and is primarily responsible for the teak hill fund’s investment portfolio management   he has extensive experience in the global credit markets prior to launching thf varkki was the portfolio manager and a director of the gartmore alphagen credit fund now the teak hill fund and was primarily responsible for the daytoday management of the fund’s investment portfolio since august    prior to joining gartmore he spent approximately  years on the sellside first at salomon brothers and then at goldman sachs while at goldman sachs varkki was a managing director serving in various roles including cohead of global high yield research head of european and asian credit research and head of global credit strategy varkki was a topranked analyst in the institutional investor allamerica fixed income research team from  to  and again in  the  and  euro money credit research polls named the teams led by varkki as topranked in credit research and in highgrade and highyield credit strategy respectively   varkki was significantly involved in proprietary credit trading activities both at goldman sachs and salomon brothers varkki’s work in the real time index area has been awarded us and european patents and is the basis of one of the largest fixed income etfs the ishares  investment grade corporate bond fund his work in industry has been awarded eight patents   varkki completed an mba in finance from new york university in  a phd in polymer science and engineering from the university of massachusetts in  and a be hons and ms hons in  from the birla institute of technology and science pilani india varkki is an advisory board member of the college of natural sciences at the university of massachusetts amherst   robert murray cfa principal chief compliance officer     robert murray is a principal of the firm a member of the investment committee head of fundamental research and the chief compliance officer at credit capital robert also oversees corporate credit allocations in several of the separate managed accounts and in the teak hill fund   prior to joining cci robert was most recently at wexford capital llc where he was a senior credit analyst on the credit opportunities fund prior to that he spent over  years at merrill lynch investment managers in plainsboro new jersey including eight years as a portfolio manager where he ran several high yield bond funds for retail and institutional clients earlier in his career he spent over five years at standard and poor’s in new york where he worked in both equity research and debt rating   robert received an mba in finance accounting and managerial economics from the kellogg school of management at northwestern university in  he earned the chartered financial analyst designation in  robert earned a ba in economics magna cum laude at the college of the holy cross where he was elected to phi beta kappa and received the freeman saltus prize in economics he is a member of the cfa institute the new york society of security analysts and fixed income analysts income society inc   dr suhas ketkar principal     suhas ketkar is the head of macroeconomic research and strategy at credit capital investments cci he is also the cofund manager for the ashburton india fixed income opportunities fund he is a recognized expert on the growth markets of asia latin america and europe he has a proven track record in developing predictive models of investment opportunities and risks he has relationships with economic policy makers worldwide with particularly strong contacts in the indian policy circles   suhas recently concluded his tenure as a professor of economics at vanderbilt university and president of the association of indian economic and financial studies an organization of economists interested in research on india   suhas worked as a financial economist and strategist for twentyfive years with several wall street firms at rbs greenwich capital from  through  he developed a highly profitable longshort currency investment strategy from  until  he directed economic and quantitative research with fidelity investments advising on asset allocation and management of  billion in equities and  billion in fixed income in emerging markets at credit suisse first boston  he built a well respected research team advised fixed income and equity institutional investors and helped raise  billion for emerging market issuers from  until  he helped establish exposure limits at marine midland bank and developed research on sovereign default risk   suhas holds a phd in economics from vanderbilt university and earned an ma in economics from the delhi school of economics   richard roy principal portfolio manager     richard roy is a principal portfolio manager and a member of the investment committee at credit capital investments cci   prior to joining cci richard was the founder and managing partner of lucror capital advisors lp an investment management firm focused on investments in the energy and energy infrastructure sectors   prior to that richard served as a director in citigroup investment research’s energy  energy infrastructure group while at citigroup richard advised institutions corporate and state pension funds hedge funds sovereign wealth funds mutual funds financial advisers and high net worth individuals on investing in the energy energy infrastructure and industrials complexes during his tenure at citigroup richard had direct responsibility for over  billion in equity market capitalization worked on over  billion of mlp and other energy equity offerings including the marketing of more than  initial public offerings and analyzed over  billion worth of mergers  acquisitions richard’s research has been featured in barron’s and in  he was recognized as a “top stock picker” in the united states by financial timesstarmine placing th out of  in addition he has been recognized by starmine as a topranked equity research analyst receiving  out of  stars for stocks under coverage in such categories as “eps estimate accuracy” and “industry excess return”   earlier in his career richard worked as an associate with the boutique investment bank bv murray  co and as an associate in the international private banking division of merrill lynch   richard received a bs in finance and marketing from the mcintire school of commerce at the university of virginia where he was a year varsity tennis letterman as well as a team cocaptain and an mba from columbia business school with a concentration in finance and entrepreneurship   joseph pirrello jd cpa chief financial officer     joe pirrello serves as the finance officer for the firm he oversees compliance and regulation matters for the company in addition joe oversees and prepares the company’s tax returns and is involved with the preparation of internal use financial reports of the company joe is also a partner in fortunato  pirrello llc   joe is a certified public accountant and an attorney he has over twentyfive years of tax and accounting experience he has worked with hedge funds and financial service companies in an accounting and tax advisory capacity he was a partner at wiss  co a regional accounting firm for eight years and had managed the new jersey tax practice for bdo usa a national accounting firm additionally joe has advised clients in such areas as the structuring of business organizations including the purchase or sale of a business corporate and partnership taxation establishing retirement plans and taxation of us residents working abroad he has assisted clients with international tax planning and structuring for both inbound and outbound transactions for foreign and domestic companies   he has been a professor in the accounting and taxation department of william paterson university and is a frequent guest lecturer on real estate taxation topics at new york university joe received a juris doctorate jd from seton hall university school of law and a bachelor of science bs from the university of rhode island he is a member of the tax division of the american institute of certified public accountants the new jersey society of certified public accountants and the new jersey state bar association copyright   credit capital investments llc all rights reserved credit capital investments llc home about us contact us cci snapshot team affiliations team donald tang chairman varkki chacko managing principal chief investment officer robert murray cfa principal chief compliance officer dr suhas ketkar principal richard roy principal portfolio manager joseph pirrello j